    <item>
      <title>World cup final — three takeaways</title>
      <link>https://old.example.com/2026/01/world-cup-final-takeaways/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jan 2026 22:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[jane@example.com]]></dc:creator>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://old.example.com/?p=101</guid>
      <description></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>What a final. Here's what stood out beyond the headline result.</p><h2>1. The midfield made the game</h2><p>Possession lopsided in the first half but the press tightened after the break.</p><h2>2. Goalkeepers were the difference</h2><p>Three world-class saves on each side kept the score tight until extra time.</p><h2>3. The winning goal — and why it matters</h2><p>Set-piece routines win tournaments. The losing side will study this for years.</p>]]></content:encoded>
      <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Three observations from the world cup final that go beyond the score line.]]></excerpt:encoded>
