    <item>
      <title>Pasta carbonara — the truth</title>
      <link>https://old.example.com/2026/01/pasta-carbonara-truth/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jan 2026 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin@example.com]]></dc:creator>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://old.example.com/?p=102</guid>
      <description></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The original recipe has four ingredients. <strong>No cream. No mushrooms. No peas.</strong></p><p><img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/wprecipes/640/360" alt="Pasta carbonara on a plate" /></p><h2>Ingredients</h2><ul><li>400 g spaghetti</li><li>200 g guanciale</li><li>4 large egg yolks + 1 whole egg</li><li>80 g Pecorino Romano, finely grated</li></ul><p>Black pepper to finish. That's it. Anyone telling you to add cream is selling you a different dish.</p>]]></content:encoded>
      <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A no-cream, four-ingredient carbonara — and a quick note on why cream-loving versions miss the point.]]></excerpt:encoded>
      <wp:post_id>102</wp:post_id>
